# Project Architecture — Omni-channel Chat System

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Backend | Frontend |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Framework | NestJS 11 | Next.js 16 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript 5.7 | TypeScript 5 |
| Database | PostgreSQL + TypeORM 0.3 | — |
| Auth | JWT (passport-jwt, bcrypt) | Zustand persist + axios interceptor |
| Realtime | Socket.IO (namespace `/chat`) | socket.io-client |
| Validation | class-validator / class-transformer | zod + react-hook-form |
| HTTP Client | axios (for LINE/FB/IG/Shopee/Lazada APIs) | axios |
| State | — | Zustand (auth, chat stores) + TanStack React Query v5 |
| UI | Swagger at `/api` | Tailwind CSS v4, lucide-react icons |

## Backend Directory Layout (`chat-backend/`)

```
src/
  main.ts                         # Bootstrap, CORS, Swagger, ValidationPipe, GlobalExceptionFilter
  app.module.ts                   # Root module, imports all feature modules
  app.controller.ts / .service.ts
  data-source.ts                  # TypeORM CLI datasource (migrations)
  config/
    configuration.ts              # Env mapping → structured config keys
  common/
    errors/                       # AppException, ErrorCode enum
    filters/                      # GlobalExceptionFilter (HTTP)
  entities/
    index.ts                      # Re-exports all entities + enums
    shop.entity.ts                # Shop (shop_id, shop_name)
    platform.entity.ts            # Platform (platform_type enum: LINE|FACEBOOK|INSTAGRAM|SHOPEE|LAZADA)
    credential.entity.ts          # Credential (tokens per platform)
    customer-identity.entity.ts   # CustomerIdentity (external_user_id, display_name, avatar_url)
    user.entity.ts                # User (username, password, role: USER|ADMIN)
    user-platform.entity.ts       # UserPlatform (assigns user to platform)
    room.entity.ts                # Room (customer_identity + platform, unread_count, status)
    room-member.entity.ts         # RoomMember (user in room, role: PRIMARY|SECONDARY|OBSERVER)
    chat.entity.ts                # Chat (message, direction IN/OUT, sender_type, message_type, metadata JSONB)
    chat-read-receipt.entity.ts   # ChatReadReceipt (user read tracking)
  migrations/                     # TypeORM migrations (timestamp-prefixed)
  modules/
    auth/        → AuthController, AuthService, JwtStrategy, JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard
    shop/        → CRUD for shops
    platform/    → CRUD for platforms
    credential/  → CRUD for credentials (tokens)
    user/        → CRUD for users
    user-platform/ → assign users to platforms
    room/        → CRUD for rooms + members
    customer-identity/ → CRUD + findOrCreate
    chat/        → ChatController, ChatService, ChatGateway, ChatEmitterService
    line/        → LineMessagingService (push/reply/profile), LineWebhookService
    facebook/    → FacebookMessagingService, FacebookWebhookService
    instagram/   → InstagramMessagingService, InstagramWebhookService
    shopee/      → ShopeeMessagingService, ShopeePollingService (stub)
    lazada/      → LazadaMessagingService, LazadaPollingService (stub)
    webhooks/    → WebhooksController (LINE/FB/IG/Shopee/Lazada webhook endpoints)
```

## Frontend Directory Layout (`chat-frontend/`)

```
app/
  layout.tsx          # Root layout (Thai font, QueryProvider)
  page.tsx            # Redirect → /chat
  globals.css         # Tailwind v4 theme
  login/page.tsx      # Login page (react-hook-form + zod)
  chat/
    layout.tsx        # AuthProvider + Sidebar + useSocket init
    page.tsx          # Empty state "select a room"
    [roomId]/page.tsx # ChatWindow for selected room
components/
  chat/               # ChatBubble, ChatInput, ChatWindow, RoomItem, Sidebar, TypingIndicator
  layout/             # AdminProfile
  ui/                 # Avatar, Badge, Button, Input, PlatformIcon, Spinner
hooks/
  useAuth.ts          # useLogin, useLogout, useShops
  useMessages.ts      # useInfiniteQuery for chat messages
  useRooms.ts         # useQuery for room list
  useSocket.ts        # Socket.IO hook (join/leave room, typing, mark read)
lib/
  axios.ts            # Axios instance with auth interceptor + retry
  socket.ts           # Socket.IO singleton (namespace /chat)
  cn.ts               # clsx + tailwind-merge
  error-codes.ts      # Error code → Thai message mapping
providers/
  AuthProvider.tsx     # Route guard (redirect to /login if no token)
  QueryProvider.tsx    # TanStack QueryClient
stores/
  auth.store.ts       # Zustand persist: token, userId, role, activeShopId
  chat.store.ts       # Zustand: activeRoomId, platformFilter, typingUsers
schemas/
  auth.schema.ts      # Zod login schema
  chat.schema.ts      # Zod send message schema
types/
  api.ts              # TypeScript interfaces (Room, Chat, Platform, etc.)
```

## Key Entity Relationships

```
Shop 1──N Platform 1──N Credential
                    1──N CustomerIdentity 1──N Room 1──N Chat 1──N ChatReadReceipt
                    1──N UserPlatform N──1 User 1──N RoomMember N──1 Room
```

## Core API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|---------|
| POST | /auth/login | Public | JWT login |
| POST | /chats/webhook/inbound | Public | Inbound message pipeline (LINE-shaped payload) |
| POST | /chats/send | JWT | Admin sends message → DB + platform + WebSocket |
| GET | /chats/room/:roomId/detailed | JWT | Paginated messages with sender names |
| GET | /rooms | Open | List rooms (optional platformId filter) |
| POST | /webhooks/line | Public | LINE webhook receiver |
| POST | /webhooks/facebook | Public | Facebook webhook |
| POST | /webhooks/instagram | Public | Instagram webhook |

## WebSocket Events (namespace: `/chat`)

| Direction | Event | Payload |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| Client→Server | join_room | { roomId } |
| Client→Server | leave_room | { roomId } |
| Client→Server | send_message | { roomId, message, messageType } |
| Client→Server | typing | { roomId, isTyping } |
| Client→Server | mark_read | { roomId } |
| Server→Client | new_message | Chat object |
| Server→Client | typing | { roomId, userId, username, isTyping } |
| Server→Client | messages_read | { roomId, userId } |
| Server→Client | room_updated | { roomId, ...partial room data } |

## Inbound Message Flow

```
External Platform → POST /chats/webhook/inbound (or /webhooks/line)
  → Find Platform by destination (external_account_id)
  → FindOrCreate CustomerIdentity
  → FindOrCreate Room
  → Add RoomMembers (from UserPlatform)
  → Upsert Chat record
  → Emit via ChatEmitterService (new_message + room_updated)
```

